{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351809077,"sessionID":"ses_31c00d8c6ffeD56RZfp762dPPU","part":{"id":"prt_ce40122b7002721uenKY8vVN9s","sessionID":"ses_31c00d8c6ffeD56RZfp762dPPU","messageID":"msg_ce4011b65001i2nnuXEGUrly7f","type":"text","text":"The `logs` command doesn't need config or features file — it just reads from `.wombo-logs/`. Let me check that the command is placed correctly by verifying it doesn't require config loading. Looking at the code flow, the `logs` case is inside the switch that's after config loading. However, `logs` shouldn't require config — let me handle this by placing it before the config loading section, similar to `init` and `upgrade`:","time":{"start":1773351809077,"end":1773351809077}}}
