{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351923620,"sessionID":"ses_31c00d8c6ffeD56RZfp762dPPU","part":{"id":"prt_ce402cdd10025oD7E3YcyQz3H7","sessionID":"ses_31c00d8c6ffeD56RZfp762dPPU","messageID":"msg_ce402c672001Bj5tNwZb6ps2k5","type":"text","text":"Implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Feature: `wombo logs <feature-id>` command\n\n**Files created:**\n- `src/commands/logs.ts` — The main logs command implementation\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `src/index.ts` — Added import, arg parsing (`--tail`, `--follow`/`-f`), CLI routing, help text, and usage examples\n- `src/lib/schema.ts` — Registered the `logs` command in the schema registry for `wombo describe`\n\n### Capabilities implemented:\n1. **`wombo logs <feature-id>`** — Pretty-prints log files from `.wombo-logs/<feature-id>.log` with colorized output (errors in red, warnings in yellow, success in green, timestamps in cyan)\n2. **`--output json`** — Outputs structured JSON with `feature_id`, `log_file`, `line_count`, and `lines` array\n3. **`--tail N`** — Shows only the last N lines\n4. **`--follow` / `-f`** — Streams new output as it arrives (like `tail -f`), polling every 250ms. In follow mode, the file doesn't need to exist yet (waits for it to appear)\n5. **Helpful error messages** — When the log file doesn't exist, shows the path, explains that logs are created during headless agent runs, and suggests checking `.wombo-logs/` or running `wombo launch` first\n6. **No config required** — The `logs` command is placed before config loading, so it works even without `wombo.json`","time":{"start":1773351923620,"end":1773351923620}}}
